.TH "drmm_vram_helper_init" 9 "drmm_vram_helper_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drmm_vram_helper_init \- Initializes a device's instance of &struct drm_vram_mm
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drmm_vram_helper_init
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "uint64_t vram_base "  ","
.BI "size_t vram_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the DRM device
.IP "vram_base" 12
the base address of the video memory
.IP "vram_size" 12
the size of the video memory in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a new instance of \fIstruct drm_vram_mm\fP and stores it in
struct \fIdrm_device.vram_mm\fP. The instance is auto-managed and cleaned
up as part of device cleanup. Calling this function multiple times
will generate an error message.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or a negative errno code otherwise.
